{
  "texts": [
    "In this paper, a bipartite graph, 𝐺 𝑉, 𝐸, 𝑨 is constructed to describe the user-tweet relationship, where 𝑉 denotes the vertices, and 𝐸denotes the edges.",
    "When a user 𝑈 performs an action on a source tweet 𝑇, there is an edge between them.",
    "Mathematically, the relationship between users and source tweets can be denoted by an adjacency matrix.",
    "For information propagation module, each source tweet 𝑇 consists of 𝑚 comments with a tree structure of information diffusion, denoted by 𝐶, 𝐶, ⋯, 𝐶.",
    "We use $𝐺 𝑉, 𝐸, 𝑨 to denote the tree structure."
  ]
}